The paper discusses learning algorithms for Bayesian nets, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on optimizing performance criteria suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) due to the use of Bayesian nets in modeling network structures.
